The paper proposes a novel approach for semi-supervised domain adaptation using a few-shot model. The method involves optimizing the conditional entropy of unlabeled target data with respect to the classifier and feature encoder. This work is likely to be relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
